e%20of%20laterite%2C%20a%20native%20Mahabaleshwar%20stone.%20Inside%2C%20we%20avoided%20cement%20completely%20and%20used%20lime%20instead.%20We%20built%20the%20entire%20house%20ourselves%2C%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us%2C%20with%20our%20own%20hands%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Momo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20home%20is%20entirely%20solar-powered.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20net%20zero%20in%20terms%20of%20electricity%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20explain.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20tiny%20house%2C%20so%20it%20does%20not%20take%20up%20too%20much%20space%2C%20and%20everything%20was%20designed%20using%20passive%20solar%20principles%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERainwater%20harvesting%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20runoff%20from%20the%20roof%20is%20captured%20and%20stored%20in%20tanks%2C%20then%20directed%20to%20irrigate%20the%20food%20forest%2C%E2%80%9D%20her%20husband%20says.%20Even%20wastewater%20is%20carefully%20managed.%20%E2%80%9COur%20greywater%2C%20from%20the%20bath%20and%20kitchen%20sink%2C%20passes%20through%20reed%20beds%2C%20where%20it%20is%20naturally%20filtered%2C%20and%20then%20it%20goes%20to%20water%20our%20banana%20plants%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20goes%20to%20waste.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20compost%20all%20our%20kitchen%20scraps%20and%20return%20them%20to%20the%20farm.%20Everything%20stays%20within%20the%20system%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELet%20nature%20lead%3A%20Planting%20a%20food%20forest%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20mission%20was%20to%20restore%20the%20land%20using%20permaculture%20practices%2C%20to%20let%20nature%20lead%20the%20way%2C%20and%20to%20enhance%20the%20space%20into%20an%20abundant%20farm%20where%20food%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20care%20could%20flourish%20side%20by%20side.%20Their%20long-term%20vision%20extended%20beyond%20just%20growing%20their%20own%20food%3B%20they%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20model%20of%20living%20that%20honoured%20the%20en